titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Henry Adams La Farge Papers Relating to a Catalogue Raisonné of Works by John La Farge
La Farge (Henry Adams) Papers Relating to a Catalogue Raisonné of Works by John La Farge
titlestmt.author: by Beinecke staff

did.unittitle: Henry Adams La Farge papers relating to a catalogue raisonné of works by John La Farge

repository.corpname: Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library

did.abstract: The collection consists of material created and accumulated by Henry Adams La Farge and others in the course of researching and compiling an unpublished catalogue raisonné of works by the American artist John La Farge. Material includes descriptive text and photographic reproductions of La Farge's works in various media, including oil paintings, drawings, watercolors, glass, and engravings; extensive correspondence files relating to the provenance of works by La Farge; and research and other files consisting of lists, catalogs, slides, photographs, correspondence, notes and other material. The collection documents the scope, history, and provenance of works of art by John La Farge, as well as the process of producing a catalogue raisonné.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection received a preliminary level of processing, including rehousing, minimal organization, and listing of contents, upon receipt by the Library. In 2007-2008, the contents list was migrated to comply with current archival descriptive standards. Further rehousing and description was carried was out in 2012.

As a rule, descriptive information found in the Collection Contents section is drawn in large part from information supplied with the collection and from an initial survey of the contents. Folder titles appearing in the contents list below are often based on those provided by the creator or previous custodian. Titles have not been verified against the contents of the folders in all cases. Otherwise, folder titles are supplied by staff during initial processing.
This finding aid may be updated periodically to account for new acquisitions to the collection and/or revisions in arrangement and description.

bioghist.head: Henry Adams La Farge (1902-1985)
bioghist.p: Henry Adams La Farge (1902-1985), grandson of the American artist John La Farge, was an art administrator, historian, and editor. He edited the book Lost Treasures of Europe: 427 Photographs (1946) and compiled a catalogue raisonné of works by John La Farge that was never published.

bioghist.head: John La Farge (1835-1910)
bioghist.p: John La Farge (1835-1910), American painter, muralist, stained-glass designer, and writer.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of material created and accumulated by Henry Adams La Farge and others in the course of researching and compiling an unpublished catalogue raisonné of works by the American artist John La Farge. Material includes descriptive text and photographic reproductions of La Farge's works in various media, including oil paintings, drawings, watercolors, glass, and engravings; extensive correspondence files relating to the provenance of works by La Farge; and research and other files consisting of lists, catalogs, slides, photographs, correspondence, notes and other material. The collection documents the scope, history, and provenance of works of art by John La Farge, as well as the process of producing a catalogue raisonné.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: I. John La Farge Catalogue Raisonné Material. II. Sale, Provenance, and Research Material. III. Provenance Correspondence. IV. Other Research and Correspondence Files.

did.unittitle: John La Farge Catalogue Raisonné Material

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized under the following headings: Oil Paintings, Drawings, Watercolors, Decorative Watercolors, Glass, Engravings, and Miscellaneous Decoration.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series I consists of descriptive text and photographic reproductions of La Farge's works in various media, including oil paintings, drawings, watercolors, glass, and engraving. The numbering schemes for works in various media are those devised by the creator.
